						               													<description>Abstract game for two players. Best played on a Reversi board, can be extended over a 19x19 Goban.&amp;#10;rules:&amp;#10;1) players place alternately one piece on the board &amp;#10;2) pieces on the board influence their cell and all the cells along horizontal, vertical and  diagonal lines, up to the first occupied cell included.&amp;#10;3) a player can occupy a cell if the number of pieces of him influencing that cell is equal or higher than that of the opponent; if the cell is empty, that player occupies it with one of his pieces, if it's occupied by the opponent, the player will change that piece with one of his pieces.&amp;#10;4) when a player has no more available moves, he must pass the turn to his opponent&amp;#10;5) game is over when both player have no more moves&amp;#10;6) the winner is the player with the higher number of pieces on the board when the game is over&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A &amp;quot;pie rule&amp;quot; is recommender for the opening (first player has a clear advantage); otherwise, a compensation (like Komi in Go) should be used (TBD)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
